race.comment: SUPER MIRAGE (1) hasn't been far away of late, having his first run for the Bedggood yard at Pakenham over 1600m last time, okay there despite finishing fifth at $2.45. Up in trip can suit now, look for improvement in a winnable race. OLNEY (9) has been close up his past couple, third in this grade at Cranbourne last time. He maps for every chance trailing the speed and can break through. OUR PARAMOUR (5) wasn't beaten far at Seymour last time and will be hard to hold out if the tempo is on but will likely give them a start. SINHALESE (2) won well fresh at Yarra Valley to break his maiden and might be able to go on with it this time in.
